Enum Operation

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Operation>
      • Ex1.Operation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Operation>

    public enum Operation
extends java.lang.Enum<Operation>
    This enum presents the set of operations applicable on function to compose a complex function from two functions. E.g., Plus: plus(f1(x), f2(x)), Times: mul(f1(x), f2(x)), Divid: div(f1(x), f2(x)), Max: max(f1(x), f2(x)), Min: min(f1(x), f2(x)), Comp: comp(f1(x), f2(x)) == f1(f2(x)) None representing no Operation and Error representing an unknown (aka unsupported) Operation.
    Author:
    boaz_benmoshe
